animal.description:
www.TheLastResortRescue.com PLEASE NOTE: IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET THE FIRST STEP IS TO FILL OUT OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AVAILABLE AT THELASTRESORTRESCUE.COM. If you have a question or inquiry please email us at tlrapplications@gmail.com
GOT TOYS?? Donovan was found as a stray at the tender age of 5 months. Being a black pittie mix and not a "baby, baby", Donovan sat in the shelter for 3 months. Unable to exercise, Donovan began to become overly frustrated. We had met and worked with Donovan on a trip to GA and knew he had tremendous amounts of potential... so... Donovan became a TLR dog. Donovan is living with our resident trainer, and spent a week at the esteemed Peaceable Paws basic manners training academy. He knows his cues well. Sit, down, targeting, he walks well on a leash. Donovan is toy and treat motivated. He is still working on his impulse control and will need a human dedicated to continuing his force free training. (His foster mom and our resident trainer will provide sessions at no charge!) Due to his exuberance Donovan will be best right now in an adult home, and likely as an only child. Please know that Donovan is EVERYTHING friendly, he just needs to continue to work on himself!! Donovan would love a friendly, high energy person to call his own. He would play, hike, run, whatever all day with his person. Or just hang out on the couch and watch TV!!!! He is still a young guy at just a year old, and hasn't had the opportunity to develop into the dog we know he can be. So, if you are looking for a special dog, who loves all things, and you don't mind squeaky toys... come meet Donovan!!!!

animal.description: This beautiful jewel of a dog is Jewel! Around 10 months old, Jewel is a Lab mix, but definitely has something smaller in her breed mix because she's a pocket sized Lab at only 40 lbs. It's possible she also has some Hound in her because she talks like a Hound dog. A little skittish around new people and in new situations, once she warms up, it doesn't take long for her to find your lap. She is housetrained when she has access to a yard and would likely be happiest in a home with a yard to run around in. She loves to play with tennis balls and rope toys and enjoys playing fetch. She would love a dog sibling in her forever home to play with, but the dog sibling should be tolerant of dogs that will get up in your face like a puppy. We are also told Jewel has done okay around cats. She is smart and knows a few basic commands but is still brushing up on her manners such as puppy nibbling and her leash skills. She would prefer a family that works from home and/or is home more often that not. She is working on learning it's ok for her family to leave her home alone for short periods and will need a family dedicated to continuing that training with her. If you think you are ready to add to your family by adopting Jewel, then fill out an adoption application on our website today! We recommend completing the application process and connecting with a adoption coach before looking for a dog or puppy you'd like to adopt. If you're already approved to adopt or if you've adopted from Labs and More before, connect with your adoption coach for the next steps. Your interest in adopting a rescued dog or puppy from Labs and More Rescue is appreciated! Please find our adoption information at www.labsandmore.org. Your adoption donation provides funding for Labs and More, a nonprofit organization which is supported solely by Volunteers and funded by donations. Good news is your adoption donation can be considered tax deductible. So much care is provided to your new dog prior to the adoption, including: spay and neuter, microchip, veterinarian visit(s), vaccinations, and other medical care as needed. Many of the dogs we rescue require extensive surgeries and care prior to adoption. Please understand we are unable to predict future behavior or medical needs of your adopted dog. We provide no guarantees regarding behavior, breed, or age of the dogs. Thank you for rescuing.Thank you for looking to Adopt a Labrador Retriever or other Mixed Breed Dog from California Labradors Retrievers and More Rescue. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. If you have any questions email us at doginfo@labsandmore.org or call us at 858-273-5386. Thank you for looking to a rescue group to fulfill your dream of adding a new dog to your life! Dogs + Love = Family

animal.description:
Adorable Buddy, is an approx. 1 year old, Boxer mix, YOUNG boy, in a brown golden suit, with a striking white chest! He is so frigging cute and Handsome! Look at all those adorable wrinkles in his cute face! He is one big puppy goofball!
He is doing great with all the dogs we've introduced him to at the rescue. He came in with lots of puppy energy and is doing great learning the ropes. He does like to PLAY box sometimes, as he is young and he is hysterical playing and running through the fields with happy joy! He's been great with the female Dixie, who he met at the shelter and they run silly in the field, jumping, running and playing. HE gets along with the Conner, the male chunky Staffordshire, out in the play yards, not causing any young dog mischief.
He is a new rescue for Christmas before the shelter closed for a 2 week holiday. So we are really just getting to know him in the play yards and out for walks. 
We dont know all the fun things he longs to do just yet, but he does love to jump around like a puppy and play around. Active, lifestyle with obedience knowledge will allow him to thrive and be all he can be and thrive! He is adorable!. 
He is listed as a one year old Boxer mix from the shelter, with his fun ears, as one is always up, saying hello! He is quiet, doesnt bark or cause any issues.
He should have a knowledgeable handler, helping him with his young energy and all the love he has to give. He will do awesome in fun obedience classes and loves cookies and treat motivated. You will be able to go anywhere with him after training to learn all his puppy manners.. He currently plays with male and female dogs. We do not recommend super young children as he might not realize they are there and knock them over.
We have more pics put need to process them to post but wanted to get at least one of his Santa Claus adorable pics up so he can find his new forever home for the New Year!.
He is learning his trail walking and will be an excellent snuggler with proper exercise and mental stimulation  games! 
   He gets along with lots of dogs,  he is handsome and a great adoption pick for you and or a family!
So handsome in his golden coat and black muzzle.
He is neutered, up to date on vaccines, and micro-chipped. All he needs now is his forever loving home! If you are interested in adopting him, please fill out an application today.

animal.description: Hello my name is Gabe, but I actually think my name should be ""Lucky"". A couple weeks before Christmas, a Good Samaritan found me inside a garbage bag abandoned near the side of a road. I would have died in a bag if it wasn't for that hero. I'm so friendly and super sweet. I still have a lot of puppy in me, but can be dog selective. I'm not sure how I would do with children, so maybe older kids would be best for me. I would love to have a fenced in yard to play ball. I'm looking forward to finding my forever home!

animal.description: Maple and her buddy, Teak, were rescued up in Riverside as strays. Shortly after being scooped up, Maple gave birth to a litter of pups, who were quickly adopted out. Since she was a shy and scared girl, Maple didn't quite have the same luck...making her the ideal candidate for foster. After a few short weeks, Maple has completely transformed - she went from cowering in the corner with her tail perpetually tucked to happily approaching her foster mama for pets and enjoying a game of chase with her foster siblings. Though still a bit nervous, she now comfortably settles in for snuggles on the couch, doling out sweet little licks to request pets. Clocking in at about 11lbs, this quiet girl will do fine with any living situation. She is crate-trained and (mostly) house-trained, with only a few accidents that are easily avoidable with a quick jaunt outside after naptime and playtime. Maple will need a doggy companion, so she can continue to learn how to be a confident pup.To initiate the adoption process for this dog, please complete our online application by clicking below. Your adoption coordinator will respod to you via email once they receive your application: www.thebarkinglot.net/adopt

animal.description: Teak and his lady friend, Maple, were rescued up in Riverside as strays. Behind his initially petrified exterior, he is a fun-loving dude who has been THRIVING in foster. Teak is a liiiiittle bit naughty, but in the cutest sense of the word - that's what gives him his charm! His favorite activity is darting around the house, casually moving his foster mama's house slipper when she's not looking. Teak's leash-walking skills are improving by the day, though he is still nervous when cars drive by. With his small size of 8lbs, he doesn't need a ton of exercise and would do great with apartment living. His foster mama has only ever heard him bark once. ***All animals listed on our website are in private foster homes. To arrange a meet and greet with a dog, you MUST fill out the adoption application so that it can be sent to the foster parent for review to determine if your home is a match for the dog. If a dog receives multiple applications, we operate on a best-fit basis, not first come first served.***

**Needs a home with another dog, or people that are essentially around all the time.**

Jordy is a curious and rambunctious middle aged (6 yrs old) man, who has had a hard life prior to coming to his foster home. While we don't know much, we know he and his brother (Ben Lee) ended up in the shelter after his owner died. He loves his morning under his chin rubs, and a slow stroll. While he was initially very nervous when coming to his foster home, he has quickly warmed to the house's dog and people. A fully potty trained pup, Jordy also loves his crate and soft places to sleep. He can be a vocal dog when left alone or when other dogs aren't paying attention to him, so his future forever home should have another dog or a family that's home often. He loves being pet and scratched, as long as you don't start with the top of his head!

Jordy is neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations, microchipped, has been dewormed, and is current on his monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. His adoption fee is $300. If you think he could be the one for you, please fill out and adoption application on our website: www.secondchancenc.org. Thank you!

***I am not non-shedding or low-shedding***

**Luna is Deaf. Luna is looking for a home as an only dog for the time being. She seems to do well with other dogs that match her energy and are submissive, but doesn't mesh well with cranky/dominant dogs because she cannot hear their warnings and continues to try to play, which escalates at times.**

Luna is a 16 month old, mixed breed dog of about 50 pounds. Despite being a Deaf dog she doesn't let that hold her back from tackling life. She is full of energy, curiosity, and has lots of love to give. Luna would do best with an experienced owner with skills of training a deaf dog to help channel her energy. Luna loves her backyard where she chases squirrels, digs holes and runs up and down the fence talking to next door dogs. Luna is house trained, crate trained and settles in each night with her treat ball in the crate. Luna has learned several hand commands and wears a training collar to which she responds to vibration instructions. Luna loves new human friends. She is a big supporter of snuggles and loves belly rubs.

Luna is spayed, up-to-date on vaccinations, microchipped, has been dewormed, and is current on her monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventatives. Her adoption fee is $300. If you think she could be the one for you, please fill out an adoption application on our website: www.secondchancenc.org.

animal.description:
Marilyn's heartbreaking story :( 

Last summer Marilyn was found unconscious on a dirt road. She was severely under weight. Her skin and coat was very unhealthy from lack of nutrition and suspected filthy living conditons. Based on the horrific condition of her breast she was likely used for breeding. She had a serious wound on her head that indicates she was hit very hard, probably with intentions of hurting her. She was heartworm positive. Depressed, scarred and scared, you could see fear, betrayal and uncertainty in her eyes. Discouraged but not defeated. This girl is a survivor!

Today Marilyn is healthy and thriving in her foster home. She completed HW treatment and has been spayed. Also housebroken, leash & crate trained. Marilyn is a super sweet, friendly, outgoing, loving "strong" playful girl. Craves love and attention, thinks she's a lap dog, and wants to be included in everything. Marilyn has such an adorable personality and likes to "help" when you take the blanket out of her kennel to fluff it up. She grabs it, pulls it back in, and fluffs it up herself. If any sweet soul deserves comfort, peace and a lifetime of love, it is Marilyn. 

Marilyn will make an ideal companion. She loves to snuggle on a couch and be close to her human. She gets very excited around cats so we feel that's not ideal for her forever home. Her foster family introduces her on a leash to new dogs and puppies so she is not startled. Mari-lynn as we call her, longs for a family of her own.

animal.description:
If fluff isnt your thing, we have the perfect pup for you. Meredith is a 4-month-old, 20-pound Lab mix. Shes playful and Velcro, always following her person around. She doesnt have the crazy energy of some of her Aussie foster siblings, but will watch and join in the fun when they are finally slowing down. She likes to wrestle with them and play tug-of-war or snuggle with her stuffed animals.

Meredith sleeps quietly all night in her crate, is learning to walk on a leash, and is working on potty training. She has learned to sit and will hop into her crate on command.

Like most puppies, Meredith can be a little nippy. She also can get possessive of her food around other dogs. Shed do best in a home where someone has time to work on puppy training and who has lots of snuggles for a sweet girl.

Meredith is up to date on vaccinations, spayed, microchipped, and current on heartworm/flea and tick prevention. Also included in her adoption is a Fi GPS collar and one year of GPS service subscription. If she were to escape, as soon as she leaves the safe zone you set around your home, you are alerted
so that you can find Meredith's whereabouts. Youll also be able to see how many steps per day she takes to ensure she gets the right amount of exercise, alongside many other features to explore in the Fi mobile app.

animal.description:
Meet Oliver! Oliver is a senior chihuahua who is looking to live out his golden years in a home filled with love and cuddles. Although estimated to be 10-12 yrs old, he is a playful and easygoing boy who gets along great with the 4 other dogs, 3 cats and a young child in his foster home. Oliver is currently working on potty training and is doing well! However, he is a marker so a belly band is recommended for him. He does great in his kennel while his foster parents are at work and overnight to help with potty training. 

Oliver has a few health challenges. He tested weak positive for heartworms which he is currently being treated for and he also has a significant heart murmur (grade 5/6) for which he'll need to take lifelong medication (Enalapril). He definitely doesn't let these conditions get him down though! He's all love and looking for the perfect home to share it with.

Does well with other dogs, kids, and cats.

Oliver will come with age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, deworming, heartworm medication, heart medication, and neutered. His adoption fee is $0, sponsored by a dog-loving family.

Apply to adopt at https://forms.gle/Tc2jvVQ1oYjPSwmeA.

Visit our website at www.lucky13rescue.org.

animal.description:
Princess has a great personality and disposition ~ She is good with other dogs that are good with her.

She does not mind loud noise
She LOVES to go on walks
She LOVES tennis balls
She likes stuffed animals but she wants to bury them immediately
She is playful (especially for her age)
She prefers to be inside
She is very kickback. Give her a bed and she is happy. She will just stay on it unless she wants something (a drink, potty, etc.)
She is potty trained, she will go to the door
She is VERY smart. She learned how to use a dog door quickly
She likes car rides and does well on them

In short, for somebody that wants an indoor companion animal she is perfect. All she requires is a potty area that she has access to or can get access to with the help of a family member. Her preference would be somebody that wants to get a little exercise and take her walking but again, she is also content just laying around and playing with her tennis ball. She is pretty easy! <3

animal.description:
This sweet girl could also use a foster KINLEY UPDATE!!

Meet Kinley... This pretty girl was owner surrendered to a local overcrowded shelter when her family could no longer care for her. We believe Kinley is a Lab Mix. She’s 14 weeks old and 15.8 lbs. She is such a pretty girl. She’s your typical labby mix baby, she’s playful and goofy. She is as sweet as they come and great with other animals. She will make the perfect buddy for just about any household. Kinley does great in the house and in the crate. She is utd, dewormed and spayed. 

All dogs have a $175 adoption fee which includes vet check, age appropriate shots (atleast 2 sets for puppies), dewormer, heartworm test (if over 6 months), rabies (if atleast 16 weeks) and spay/neuter! Puppies will be altered before adoption. All rescues and shelters practice pediatric spay and neuter. This is essential in our rescue efforts and it is a policy that we will stick by. All dogs over 8 weeks and 2 pounds will be altered before adoption. There are no exceptions to this rule on all healthy and adoptable dogs. 

Puppies/Dogs that are not available for adoption due to vetting not being complete can be reserved with an approved application and a non refundable $50 deposit. This deposit is applied to your adoption fee and the remaining $125 is due at pick up.

Wags and Whiskers is an all-volunteer rescue. We also have full-time jobs and Families. We will try to answer all questions and applications in a timely manner. Please be patient and bear with us . Do not contact Parkway Animal Hospital as they are a vet clinic and can not answer questions on behalf of Wags and Whiskers. All questions and comments must go directly through the rescue. Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
This sweet girl, Coni, came to us all the way from Mexico! Things are bad everywhere but Mexico sees some of the worst. We assist a local rescue there in getting pups from there to South Carolina so they have a better chance of finding their forever homes.

Coni is a great mix of play and chill. She is approximately 2 yrs old and 24 lbs. She is a short girl, perfect size! She isn't timid at all & loves to play with others.  She has good manners when it comes to waiting her turn for a treat and sharing her toys. She does seem a little territorial with her food with other dogs but that's to be expected given the situation she came from. This can be corrected or can be controlled easily. 

She absolutely loves to cuddle with her person. She is doing pretty well with house training but isn't 100% yet. She is crate trained and walks fine on a leash. 
Good with other dogs but she was pretty wound up when she saw a cat. She was on leash though so it's hard to tell if she was wanting to play or chase. Not been kid tested but given her personality,  we can't imagine her not being good with kids as long as they are old enough to be respectful. 

If you are interested in Coni, please email us at tskadoptions@gmail.com to ask any questions or to request an application. 

We do adopt out of state as long as the adopter is willing to pick up their new baby if approved. 

Her adoption fee is $250 which includes:

* up to date on all vaccines
* rabies
* deworming 
* microchip 
* spay 
* on flea and heartworm prevention 
* matching martingale collar and leash

animal.description:
Angel is a sweet 10 year old shepherd mix full of love and snuggles to give! Angel has lived her whole life on a chain up until now, where she is ready to find her forever home indoors with her people. Angel is heartworm positive and will be receiving treatment, but will still be able to live a long and healthy life once she is done! Angel is very sweet and gentle and keeps a clean kennel. She is housebroken and loves to go for walks and car rides. She loves treats, laying in the sun, and being loved on! Angel would do best in a home with older kids and gets along great with other pets in the house. She is perfect for any family wanting a low activity pet that loves to be spoiled and loved on!  She is very well behaved and can be trusted to be out in the house when you’re gone without having an accident or getting into anything. She loves the couch potato life and is 60lbs of love. 

If you are interested in meeting Angel, please fill out an application via our website at https://therescueproject.net/adoption-application and we will get back to you via email once your application has been reviewed.  If you have further questions please feel free to reach out to us at adoptionstrp@gmail.com

Angel’s adoption fee is $100 and includes age appropriate vaccines, spay/neuter, microchip, deworm, heartworm testing.

Millie is a very sweet 9 month old border collie mix pup who is very active and full of energy most of the time. She is looking for someone or a family she go with on adventures hiking, walking or any outdoor activity.  Millie is good with kids, other dogs, and was raised in a home with cats when she was younger. She loves attention and to play fetch with anything all day long.  She is a very smart girl and is picking up the new routines in her foster home very quickly and is learning to be part of the pack after being an only dog for most of her life.  She wants to please and loves to be with her person. She is potty trained, but she needs some work on her leash manners.  She would need a home that can provide the proper exercise and mental stimulation for an active dog like her. 

All of our dogs are cared for in foster homes and are spayed or neutered prior to adoption. They are also vaccinated for distemper/parvo and wormed. Dogs are shown by appointment with their foster home.  Before traveling PLEASE call for availability. Call 208-681-4788 for more information or Message on FB.

animal.description:
MY NAME IS CORAL. I AM VERY SCARED AND I WANT A HOME OF MY OWN. I CAME IN WITH SOME BABIES THAT HAVE ALL FOUND GREAT HOMES. I AM NOT VERY FRIENDLY BECAUSE I WAS NOT TREATED WELL IN THE PAST. I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHAT HAS HAPPENED TO MY HOME OR MY FAMILY. WITH TIME I CAN GROW TO TRUST AGAIN. I AM FAIRLY SMART AND KNOW WHEN I CAN TRUST THE PEOPLE CARING FOR ME. I WOULD LIKE TO GO TO A CALM QUIET HOME WHERE I CAN TAKE ALL OF THE TIME I NEED TO RECOVER.

http://www.wagsandwhiskerspetrescue.com/adopt.html
Thank you so much for looking into wags and whiskers for your next family member.
All of our pets are up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested if over 6 months old and will be spayed or neutered before being allowed to go home.
Unfortunately, we don't always know the background of each dog. Some were dumped, abandoned in an empty house, left tied to a tree, picked up by animal control as strays, or simply unwanted by their owners. We ask that only serious and committed adopters apply as these dogs have suffered enough.

Sunny (12lbs) and Misty (8lbs) are 2 month old basset hound mix sisters. They are fun loving and inquisitive puppies. True to their breed, their noses are always on the ground searching for the next interesting smell. If you are looking for a cutie with ears for days to join your family, apply today. Misty's adoption fee is $400.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
FAST FACTS:
*2 Years Old - 47 Pounds
*Medium Energy: Playful and Cuddly
*No Dogs
*No Cats
*Potty & Crate Trained
*Training Required - Eager to Learn!

BIO:
Bon Jour! My name is Gadot, and if you bring the toys and snuggles, I will bring the smiles and love! I'm a silly and sweet lady with a medium energy level: I enjoy playing with toys but will calm down quickly when I can get a cuddle session in: nothing makes me happier than curling up in your lap for some quality snuggles! Since I love attention from my people the most, I would be very happy as your one-and-only furry friend (no other dogs or cats, please!) I am so gentle with people that I think I would do fine in a home with kids. I have lovely manners, as well: I am potty and crate trained; I will be your shadow when you are home, but I am fine relaxing during the day with my favorite antler or kong to keep myself entertained. I also adore blankets and will tuck myself in for a nap. I am eager to learn even more and would thrive with a family that will take me to training classes - I think it will be a lot of fun for both of us, and I am all about fun with my fam! Fill out that adoption application soon, OK? We have a lot of snuggling to do and I can't wait to get started!

ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS, NO EXCEPTIONS:
*ADOPTION FEE: $300
*Be at least 21 years of age
*Live in a 50-mile radius of Itasca, within the Illinois border
*Have the knowledge and agreement of all adults living in the household
*Have approval from owner of residence (written in lease)
*Have a valid ID with current address (please provide proof of address if ID address is not up-to-date)
*Be approved as a suitable adoptive home by Fetching Tails Foundation
*Be prepared to make a lifetime commitment

If interested please fill out an application on our website at www.fetchingtailsfoundation.org; please make sure you fill in every required field/question or your submission will not go through. Please note that we take time to learn as much as we can about each dog in our care and our bios are our current observations; we are unable to make any guarantees on the future health or temperament of your adopted dog. Most dogs in our care come with unknown pre-rescue history and as such breed and age estimates are an educated guess.

Age: 5yrs
Weight: 62 lbs
Energy level: low to moderate
Overall drive: moderate to high
Location: Puyallup, Washington

Vincent is ready to be your shadow! Ready to participate in anything and everything, this loving boy will charm you with his affectionate, social nature. If he were a human, Vincent would be a food tester; he loves food above all things and would be the best judge of which is tastiest!

Vincent is a social butterfly who loves meeting people of all ages. He does well in public places and will typically ignore people and other dogs unless approached. Vincent rarely wants to interact with other dogs. He tolerates the other dog in his foster home but does not engage in play. Due to his high prey drive, he cannot share his forever home with small animals, including cats, or small children. Vincent rides well in the car if he is confined in a crate, has done well at the veterinarian’s office, and is unfazed by loud noises, including fireworks. He has mastered basic obedience and is currently working on being away from his preferred person. Vincent does well in the crate in his foster home but is still working on staying in it calmly when left alone.

Vincent would thrive in a home where his person would spend most of their time with him. He would love to go on regular walks and hikes, and would also need someone willing to play daily (or moreso!) fetch games with him. Vincent would do great a high-speed sports such as agility or Fast Cat, if his new family might be interested. Vincent is a work of art and is ready to “Van Gogh” for you!

WEST COAST ADOPTIONS ONLY

Must have previous or current, purebred Malinois experience OR other high drive working breed experience

Our adoption process includes- completion of an application, followed by a telephone interview. If that goes well, we will arrange for a home visit.
Adoption Fee: $500.00. Transport along Interstate 5 (Bakersfield, CA to Bellingham, WA) is available but cost not included in adoption fee. 

Please visit www.woofproject.org and fill out an adoption application located here https://www.woofproject.org/application

Stoli is a sweet, loving, and easy-going dog who loves to follow his person wherever they might go. If he were smaller and had his way, he’d spend all his time in someone’s lap! If he were a human, he would be that BFF everyone wants; he will do anything he can to be around you, but if you need to be away, he waits patiently for you to come back.

Stoli has a very sweet nature and does best with gentle handling and guidance. He loves to meet people and has done well around small dogs that share his foster home. He also plays well with larger dogs, however, does not interact well with intact males of any size. Stoli rides well in the car, has done well at the veterinarian’s office, and isn’t bothered by loud noises. He will sometimes react to other dogs when out on leash, especially when around another reactive dog. However, he is easy to redirect. Stoli does not like to be crated/contained when indoors, however has done well loose in the house when his foster family has been away. He will need continued work on enforcing these boundaries to ensure he is successful at maintaining respect when unattended in the home. Stoli is currently working on mastering basic obedience.

Stoli would do best in a home that would allow him to spend the maximum amount of time with his handler. He is quiet and respectful and does well in almost any environment. He would be fine sharing his home with other dogs, but would also do well as an only pet. Stoli’s dream is to be a house/office dog, as he tires easily due to the arthritis in his rear limbs. He will jog around the yard on occasion but only if his person accompanies him. Looking for the best candidate for your team? This quiet gentleman can’t wait to be your favorite new work-from-home coworker!

animal.description:
Hello everyone! Our names are Sheba and midnight! We are both lab type mixes. We are a mommy and son bonded pair. We are fully house snd kennel trained. We have never ever had a good life. We’ve always lived on a chain and we were so very sad. We were taken from our owners and now we have the chance at getting the best lives. We were told we would never be adopted but the pals team thinks differently. We know there’s a home out there for us we just have to find it. 

The adoption donation fee is $300 which is tax-deductible and goes towards the care of homeless pets with Pals for Paws. 

To expedite the adoption process you can fill out an application online at www.palsforpawsinc.com/adopt. Please note the adoption application doesn’t bind you to anything. Pals for Paws reserves the right to refuse any adoption application for any reason and at any point in the adoption process. 

To view our other wonderful Homeless Pets visit www.palsforpawsinc.com/pet-list ALSO be sure to LIKE Pals for Paws on Facebook at www.facebook.com/palsforpaws.inc 

All Pals for Paws Rescue animals are fully vetted:
*Spayed/Neutered
*Groomed
*Shots updated plus Leptospirosis 
*Micro-chipped
*Dewormed 
*On Heart-worm prevention
*On Flea and Tick Prevention
* Dentals are done if needed 

You only need to see your vet for a “meet n greet” of your new family member and to turn in their medical records.

Pals for Paws is a 501(c)3 animal rescue. Every penny donated and every penny received through adoption fees goes right back into the organization. There are times when the volunteers have to dip into their pockets to help the animals. We do not euthanize because a pet is sick, heart-worm positive, or has a broken leg; we fix it all, big and small. We strive to go above and beyond when caring for and socializing our animals. We understand the importance of getting to know each and every animal available for adoption in an effort to place them in the most perfect home possible. 
If you are looking for a particular type of dog or have special needs, We can help! Contact us at www.palsforpawsinc.com

animal.description:
Meet Turbo! He is a 6 year old lab mix. Turbo likes to take walks and go on car rides. He loves to be around his people including 4 kids who always want to pat him or hug him. He knows sit and paw and is currently working on stay.  Has been left alone in the home for at least 3 hours without any issues (not in crate). He is a sweet big beautiful dog at around 100 pounds.

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website-?www.luckymuttsrescue.org?and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application. We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks.  You may be contacted via email if there are concerns or questions.  Once all of your information is reviewed and if your application is approved, you will be notified via email.  Submitting an application and receiving an approval does not guarantee you will be adopting the dog you applied for.  Once you move to the meet and greet process, you will be contacted by the foster family to further discuss the dog, and answer questions you may have, and if applicable, a meet and greet will be set up at our adoption center.   Meet and greets are only set up with approved applicants, and we require all members in the household to be present, as well as any current dogs in the home. 
Current Adoption Fees Are:$400+tax for puppies to 3 years old
$350+tax for ages 4-7
$250+tax for ages 8 and up
Bonded pairs vary
The adoption fee covers spay/neuter, up to date age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, general deworming, heartworm test, (if over 6  months) and a certified veterinary inspection. Please be aware, listed dog breeds are based on information provided and cannot be guaranteed.  Submitting an application for a particular dog does not guarantee that you will be the applicant chosen, we receive several applications for each dog. Our adopters are picked based on the needs of the dog, and the home we feel with best fit based on your responses to our application, vet information and landlord requirements.   Approved applicants not chosen for the dog you applied for, will be in active status for a period of six months.  We encourage you to watch Petfinder, Facebook and our website for upcoming dogs.  Should you see a dog that interests you,please send us a Facebook message or an email with your approval number.  Please be patient with us, as Lucky Mutts Rescue is run strictly by volunteers and many of us work full time jobs, have families and also foster dogs. Thank you for considering Lucky Mutts Rescue for your next furry family member!
